problem.markdown:
>>GANs are trained by having a ______________ and a _______________, two separate networks that ___________ each other.<<

[[
CNN, MLP, train after {{GANs can be trained by combining any discriminator and generator. The models do take turns, but they are competing against each other. }}
(Discriminator, Generator, compete against) {{The discriminator attempts to identify the “fakes” that the generator creates, while the generator tries to “fool” the discriminator into believing his “fakes” are real. By competing in this adversarial fashion, both are trained.}}
Discriminator, Generator, cooperate with {{The discriminator and the generator do not cooperate, but rather compete against each other.}}
]]

